1
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,040
=Love Again=

2
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 15=

3
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:54,970
I'm sorry, Ms. Nie.

4
00:01:56,130 --> 00:01:56,600
I really am.

5
00:01:58,880 --> 00:01:59,810
No need to be sorry.

6
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:03,320
I was

7
00:02:03,970 --> 00:02:04,760
diagnosed with

8
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:07,570
breast cancer ten years ago.

9
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:09,290
I had

10
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:10,850
a mastectomy.

11
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:24,290
I lost my father

12
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,290
when I was

13
00:02:28,090 --> 00:02:29,480
only a little child.

14
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:31,880
Then,

15
00:02:32,690 --> 00:02:34,370
soon after I started working,

16
00:02:35,970 --> 00:02:37,410
my brother had an accident.

17
00:02:38,970 --> 00:02:39,880
After that,

18
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:41,810
my husband fell ill

19
00:02:42,410 --> 00:02:43,370
and passed.

20
00:02:44,810 --> 00:02:45,640
And then,

21
00:02:46,610 --> 00:02:47,400
my son

22
00:02:48,010 --> 00:02:49,080
moved overseas.

23
00:02:51,570 --> 00:02:52,610
One by one,

24
00:02:54,130 --> 00:02:56,880
everyone around me slowly left me.

25
00:02:58,930 --> 00:03:00,050
Honestly,

26
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:01,810
I realized long ago

27
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:04,490
that life

28
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:08,400
is just a string of goodbyes.

29
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,370
As for death,

30
00:03:14,370 --> 00:03:15,400
I've made peace with it.

31
00:03:17,010 --> 00:03:17,930
But Mr. Zhuoran,

32
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:19,690
look at this.

33
00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:22,610
Look at my left hand.

34
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:24,280
I can only...

35
00:03:28,690 --> 00:03:29,470
raise it this high.

36
00:03:34,050 --> 00:03:35,280
Sometimes, when I walk,

37
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,400
I lose my balance.

38
00:03:43,610 --> 00:03:44,320
Death

39
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:46,730
doesn't scare me.

40
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,010
But living with this ailing body

41
00:03:51,610 --> 00:03:53,370
is what I have to face every single day.

42
00:03:55,010 --> 00:03:55,930
So, I figured

43
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:58,610
I should probably just

44
00:04:00,010 --> 00:04:00,880
keep things simple.

45
00:04:11,250 --> 00:04:32,250
What a beautiful day and scene,
yet the heavens seem so cruel.

46
00:04:33,760 --> 00:05:00,490
Who's lucky enough to enjoy
such pleasures in their own garden?

47
00:05:19,570 --> 00:05:20,320
Shen Duole.

48
00:05:21,570 --> 00:05:23,250
Why aren't you doing your homework?

49
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:24,930
Mom, come look!

50
00:05:25,250 --> 00:05:26,880
Grandpa's already on his fifth lap!

51
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,690
It's so windy out today.

52
00:05:32,690 --> 00:05:33,760
He might catch a cold.

53
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,010
Go on, get Grandpa inside.

54
00:05:36,370 --> 00:05:36,690
Mom.

55
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:38,930
Judging by his vibe,

56
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,730
he's ruminating.

57
00:05:41,490 --> 00:05:42,320
He is troubled.

58
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:44,960
So, he's just walking in circles.

59
00:05:47,010 --> 00:05:48,180
What could be troubling him?

60
00:05:49,130 --> 00:05:51,250
You wouldn't get it. He's in love.

61
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:53,840
Oh, and you do?

62
00:05:55,130 --> 00:05:55,760
Not really.

63
00:05:58,630 --> 00:05:59,880
You're in your sophomore year!

64
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:01,690
Don't get lovesick now.
Go do your homework!

65
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:03,440
Fine.

66
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:38,640
(Ten years ago,)

67
00:06:39,490 --> 00:06:41,570
(I was diagnosed with breast cancer.)

68
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:43,840
(So I had)

69
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:45,610
(a mastectomy.)

70
00:06:45,620 --> 00:06:49,330
(Chen Jingmin, Tumor Genetic
Test Report, Zijin First Hospital)

71
00:06:53,490 --> 00:06:56,370
(Honestly, I realized long ago)

72
00:06:57,730 --> 00:06:58,320
(that life)

73
00:06:59,730 --> 00:07:01,370
(is just a string of goodbyes.)

74
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:06,400
(Death)

75
00:07:07,850 --> 00:07:08,850
(doesn't scare me.)

76
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:12,010
(But living with this ailing body)

77
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:14,450
(is what I have to face
every single day.)

78
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:19,680
(So, I figured)

79
00:07:21,010 --> 00:07:22,370
(I should probably just)

80
00:07:23,730 --> 00:07:24,610
(keep things simple.)

81
00:07:42,210 --> 00:07:42,880
Trust me,

82
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:45,640
you should never
send your kids overseas.

83
00:07:46,730 --> 00:07:47,600
They're so far away.

84
00:07:47,850 --> 00:07:49,010
If something happens,

85
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:50,970
you'll be worried sick.

86
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,760
My daughter's sister-in-law,

87
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:57,090
you know her, right?

88
00:07:57,490 --> 00:07:58,400
Back home,

89
00:07:58,730 --> 00:08:01,680
she was waited on hand and foot.

90
00:08:02,490 --> 00:08:03,640
Now that she's abroad,

91
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:05,760
she has to do everything herself.

92
00:08:06,210 --> 00:08:08,260
Every time she comes back,
she's all tan and skinny.

93
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:09,520
She looks like a refugee.

94
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:11,450
That girl...

95
00:08:13,850 --> 00:08:14,560
Something's up.

96
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,280
Forget it.

97
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,210
I'm hanging up.

98
00:08:18,130 --> 00:08:19,680
I called you, and you didn't pick up.

99
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:20,920
Wow, you bought so much stuff!

100
00:08:21,450 --> 00:08:22,280
And there's more?

101
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:24,860
Let me give you a hand.

102
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:26,850
- Just lie down.
- I got it. Get some rest.

103
00:08:26,850 --> 00:08:28,280
You lied on the couch doing nothing.

104
00:08:30,090 --> 00:08:31,850
I carried all these bags myself!

105
00:08:31,850 --> 00:08:32,130
Here.

106
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,560
- Don't you think...
- Sit down.

107
00:08:34,560 --> 00:08:36,130
I'm so tired that I could pass out.

108
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:38,560
Honestly, with you,

109
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:40,800
it's the same
whether you're here or not.

110
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:41,610
Baoqin, come on.

111
00:08:42,610 --> 00:08:44,560
You could've texted me.

112
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:46,040
I didn't know you bought so much.

113
00:08:46,090 --> 00:08:47,130
What text?

114
00:08:48,970 --> 00:08:49,920
You know what?

115
00:08:50,210 --> 00:08:51,640
I fixed that shoe cabinet

116
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:52,730
by the door.

117
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:53,640
What do you want?

118
00:08:54,850 --> 00:08:55,970
A medal or something?

119
00:08:58,730 --> 00:08:59,680
Who was on the phone?

120
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:02,010
A friend of Duan's.

121
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:04,730
Duole's planning to study abroad.

122
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,800
My advice was needed.

123
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:12,290
Was it a man or a woman?

124
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:13,450
Woman.

125
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:15,370
A woman?

126
00:09:17,610 --> 00:09:18,230
Come back here.

127
00:09:27,610 --> 00:09:28,280
Listen to me.

128
00:09:29,730 --> 00:09:31,520
You should stay away from Duan.

129
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:35,140
He made some serious mistakes
when he was young.

130
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:36,500
He has issues with his conduct.

131
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,370
That was years ago.

132
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:40,090
His wife's already passed away.

133
00:09:46,850 --> 00:09:48,430
Are you just waiting for me to die too?

134
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:52,830
They're here.

135
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:55,400
Liu!

136
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:56,130
Peng!

137
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:57,640
Come on in.

138
00:09:57,880 --> 00:09:59,520
Wow, that's a lot of stuff!

139
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:00,650
Were you at the supermarket?

140
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,010
Let me help you unpack.

141
00:10:02,010 --> 00:10:03,490
No, sit down. Take a seat.

142
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,110
We don't keep flowers at home anymore.

143
00:10:05,130 --> 00:10:05,560
Go on.

144
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:07,400
It's not for you.

145
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:09,210
- It's a pretty flower.
- Sit down.

146
00:10:10,090 --> 00:10:11,730
Isn't it lovely? I just bought it.

147
00:10:12,370 --> 00:10:14,280
Baoqin, sit. Come on.

148
00:10:16,010 --> 00:10:16,850
I'm exhausted.

149
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,160
Look at this magnolia.

150
00:10:21,850 --> 00:10:23,210
It's so tough and hardy.

151
00:10:23,370 --> 00:10:25,800
It's much easier to care
for than moth orchids.

152
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:27,020
And it smells great too.

153
00:10:27,330 --> 00:10:27,760
Really?

154
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:31,210
Aren't you going to
Lina's place this afternoon?

155
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:33,880
Take it to Professor Shen
for me, will you?

156
00:10:35,010 --> 00:10:36,110
And this chicken soup, too.

157
00:10:36,610 --> 00:10:37,850
I spent the morning making it.

158
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,020
Take a taxi over, okay?

159
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:41,210
I'll cover the fare.

160
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:42,280
Peng Yulan.

161
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:45,520
Here's how I see it.

162
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:47,880
You really

163
00:10:48,330 --> 00:10:50,130
shouldn't put your eggs in one basket.

164
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:52,800
Try different options.

165
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,520
Have a few backups ready.

166
00:10:56,210 --> 00:10:56,560
Oh right.

167
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:58,090
Duan used to

168
00:10:58,920 --> 00:11:01,040
drive the forklift at our factory.

169
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:01,850
Remember him?

170
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:03,130
He was quite the looker.

171
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:05,040
His wife passed away.

172
00:11:05,490 --> 00:11:06,920
If you're even a little interested,

173
00:11:07,210 --> 00:11:07,880
I could

174
00:11:08,490 --> 00:11:09,340
fix you up with him.

175
00:11:10,010 --> 00:11:10,920
Come on, Baoqin.

176
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:11,640
Are you...

177
00:11:12,210 --> 00:11:13,130
Didn't you just say

178
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,430
not to get involved with Duan?

179
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:15,790
Because he has conduct issues?

180
00:11:20,610 --> 00:11:21,880
Hey, is everything sorted?

181
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:22,920
All done.

182
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,130
I'm heading to my room.

183
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:25,610
Peng.

184
00:11:25,970 --> 00:11:26,450
Chat away.

185
00:11:27,010 --> 00:11:27,280
Sure.

186
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:29,040
Unbelievable.

187
00:11:32,010 --> 00:11:34,850
What were you saying
about Professor Shen?

188
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:39,210
She is fine.

189
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:41,010
Why do you ask?

190
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:45,330
I heard from Lina that

191
00:11:46,490 --> 00:11:49,010
he's barely eating or drinking.

192
00:11:49,330 --> 00:11:50,610
All he does is walk in circles.

193
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:53,110
He won't respond to anything.

194
00:11:53,450 --> 00:11:54,330
He's lost his spirit.

195
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:57,760
It must have something
to do with that fairy.

196
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:01,490
Did they have a falling out?

197
00:12:01,970 --> 00:12:02,880
No idea.

198
00:12:04,090 --> 00:12:05,090
Peng Yulan, trust me.

199
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:07,040
Save the flowers for yourself.

200
00:12:08,130 --> 00:12:09,560
Enjoy growing them.

201
00:12:10,090 --> 00:12:11,800
Right? Why get yourself disappointed?

202
00:12:12,970 --> 00:12:13,760
It's so heavy.

203
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,199
And I still have to carry it back.

204
00:12:16,210 --> 00:12:18,560
Taking another taxi
would cost even more.

205
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,280
How about this?

206
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,160
Take it over there for now.

207
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:27,450
Just leave it at Lina's place.

208
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:29,970
I'll swing by every few days
to take care of it.

209
00:12:31,130 --> 00:12:32,970
Take the chicken soup too.

210
00:12:33,730 --> 00:12:36,130
Just don't tell him I made it.

211
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,550
Doing good without asking for credit?

212
00:12:41,610 --> 00:12:42,570
What is wrong with you?

213
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:45,730
Food is fuel, so people need to eat.

214
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:48,130
He needs to eat.

215
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:51,640
Didn't you say he's lost his soul?

216
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:53,280
Well, with this soup,

217
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:55,970
I'll bring his soul back.

218
00:13:01,730 --> 00:13:06,090
(A jasmine flower under a cruel sky.)
♪Such a lovely jasmine flower♪

219
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:10,450
♪Such a lovely jasmine flower♪

220
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:19,010
♪Even in a blooming garden,
none smells as sweet♪

221
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:24,560
♪I wanted to pick one and wear it♪

222
00:13:24,760 --> 00:13:32,250
♪But I feared it would not
bloom again next year♪

223
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:38,800
♪Such a perfect moment,
such a cruel heaven♪

224
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:49,640
♪Who gets to enjoy beauty
and joy in their own yard?♪

225
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:52,560
Alright, let's take a break.

226
00:13:53,130 --> 00:13:54,800
We'll continue later. Take a break.

227
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:56,130
Okay.

228
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,130
That's so sad.

229
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:00,130
Breast cancer.

230
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:06,010
Wait.

231
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:09,680
Ms. Nie had breast cancer too?

232
00:14:12,090 --> 00:14:13,040
She said it herself.

233
00:14:13,210 --> 00:14:14,370
She had it ten years ago.

234
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:16,130
She's better now.

235
00:14:16,490 --> 00:14:17,610
Still, it's scary.

236
00:14:24,130 --> 00:14:24,800
Shen...

237
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,800
Breast cancer has
a high cure rate nowadays.

238
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:31,560
But in Jingmin's case,
it had already spread.

239
00:14:31,560 --> 00:14:32,970
She didn't have a chance.

240
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:34,330
Shen.

241
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:36,210
Think about it.

242
00:14:36,730 --> 00:14:37,680
At our age,

243
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:40,330
who doesn't have
a few parts that are broken?

244
00:14:41,010 --> 00:14:41,880
That's life.

245
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:43,400
It's really not a big deal.

246
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:44,850
That's not what I meant.

247
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:47,730
You don't understand how I feel.

248
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:50,560
Now, every time I hear the word cancer,

249
00:14:51,370 --> 00:14:52,920
I feel dizzy, I swear.

250
00:14:55,730 --> 00:14:56,830
What happened with Jingmin

251
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:57,850
left me traumatized.

252
00:14:57,970 --> 00:14:58,560
Yes, of course.

253
00:15:02,210 --> 00:15:02,970
How about...

254
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:04,020
How about this?

255
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,280
For now,

256
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,730
let's not bring up cancer.

257
00:15:07,210 --> 00:15:08,450
We'll just tell Ms. Nie

258
00:15:09,730 --> 00:15:11,330
that Tian

259
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:13,850
is a bit off with her Kunqu singing.

260
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:15,330
So we want Ms. Nie

261
00:15:15,490 --> 00:15:16,590
to give her some guidance.

262
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:17,920
Tian, yes!

263
00:15:18,330 --> 00:15:19,160
That's perfect.

264
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,920
We'll set up flowers,
banners, the whole deal.

265
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:22,490
You...

266
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:24,090
Call her right now.

267
00:15:24,130 --> 00:15:24,950
We'll start singing.

268
00:15:25,010 --> 00:15:26,010
Let her hear it, yeah?

269
00:15:26,090 --> 00:15:26,449
Alright!

270
00:15:26,450 --> 00:15:27,040
Let's go sing.

271
00:15:27,330 --> 00:15:28,160
Call her.

272
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:28,950
We'll get ready.

273
00:15:29,010 --> 00:15:29,370
Okay.

274
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:29,680
Okay.

275
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:38,690
Alright, come on!

276
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:40,250
Right now,

277
00:15:40,450 --> 00:15:41,600
we're going live

278
00:15:41,650 --> 00:15:43,690
with our Kunqu consultant, Ms. Nie.

279
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,010
Let's sing it for her

280
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,360
and get her feedback, okay?

281
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:47,250
Alright.

282
00:15:48,170 --> 00:15:48,450
Great!

283
00:15:52,210 --> 00:15:52,760
Ms. Nie.

284
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,320
"Jasmine Flower" is simple,

285
00:15:55,970 --> 00:15:56,840
but in its simplicity

286
00:15:57,250 --> 00:15:58,250
is real beauty.

287
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:00,840
We're rehearsing right now.

