Yeah, let's keep going.

569
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:54,890
See, moth orchids may look pretty,

570
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:57,210
but they're really hard to keep alive.

571
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:59,320
If you want a life, go with magnolias.

572
00:28:59,930 --> 00:29:00,250
Right?

573
00:29:00,490 --> 00:29:01,450
Look at the head nurse.

574
00:29:02,170 --> 00:29:02,900
She wants a house.

575
00:29:03,410 --> 00:29:04,970
That fairy lady wants his soul.

576
00:29:05,250 --> 00:29:06,520
And even phone credit.

577
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:08,450
But Peng Yulan?
She doesn't want anything.

578
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:10,560
And the key is she makes pork knuckles

579
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:11,970
and soup too!

580
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:13,410
And they're both amazing.

581
00:29:13,410 --> 00:29:14,320
Better than any chef.

582
00:29:14,320 --> 00:29:14,860
You know why?

583
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:17,250
Because she cooks with love.

584
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:18,420
And that fairy?

585
00:29:18,690 --> 00:29:19,560
She's special.

586
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:21,320
But what's the point?

587
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:23,270
She doesn't show up in person.

588
00:29:23,500 --> 00:29:24,929
At least she's not getting in the way

589
00:29:24,930 --> 00:29:26,730
of Peng Yulan becoming
your stepmother-in-law.

590
00:29:28,410 --> 00:29:29,490
Don't be so surprised.

591
00:29:31,010 --> 00:29:32,690
Sure, moth orchids
are nice on a windowsill.

592
00:29:33,490 --> 00:29:34,030
Right? But...

593
00:29:34,450 --> 00:29:34,970
But this is

594
00:29:35,560 --> 00:29:36,210
the magnolia.

595
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:38,890
It purifies the air
when you keep it indoors.

596
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:41,080
That's a win-win situation!

597
00:29:41,490 --> 00:29:41,970
Mom.

598
00:29:42,450 --> 00:29:44,040
What kind of mindset is that?

599
00:29:44,450 --> 00:29:45,450
What's wrong with it?

600
00:29:45,930 --> 00:29:47,170
What did I say that's so bad?

601
00:29:47,490 --> 00:29:48,360
Your father-in-law

602
00:29:49,170 --> 00:29:50,080
and that fairy lady

603
00:29:50,730 --> 00:29:52,120
don't even meet face to face.

604
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:54,210
They just write letters,

605
00:29:54,890 --> 00:29:55,600
make calls,

606
00:29:55,940 --> 00:29:56,929
and sing a little opera.

607
00:29:56,930 --> 00:29:57,890
She can do

608
00:29:57,890 --> 00:29:58,760
whatever she pleases.

609
00:29:58,760 --> 00:29:59,210
And if

610
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:01,600
she wants to sing opera,
then let her sing.

611
00:30:01,890 --> 00:30:02,520
Peng Yulan

612
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:04,010
likes doing housework,

613
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:05,449
loves taking care of flowers,

614
00:30:05,450 --> 00:30:06,890
so let her do that too.

615
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:09,320
Let's be honest. At our age,

616
00:30:09,970 --> 00:30:12,210
you won't find someone
with all the good traits.

617
00:30:13,320 --> 00:30:14,490
Don't get in anyone's way.

618
00:30:14,490 --> 00:30:15,320
Take what you need.

619
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:16,560
Isn't that for the best?

620
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:19,250
Then what if Shen Qing finds someone

621
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,800
to take what he needs? How about that?

622
00:30:21,410 --> 00:30:21,890
Wait.

623
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:24,250
Did Dad put you in the living room

624
00:30:24,250 --> 00:30:25,280
or in the kitchen?

625
00:30:26,760 --> 00:30:27,040
I...

626
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:30,520
Liu Lina, I...

627
00:30:31,450 --> 00:30:31,730
I...

628
00:30:32,450 --> 00:30:33,650
You're such an ungrateful brat.

629
00:30:34,650 --> 00:30:37,520
You think I'm saying this
for Peng Yulan's sake?

630
00:30:37,970 --> 00:30:40,360
I'm thinking about you.

631
00:30:40,970 --> 00:30:42,890
Peng Yulan can run
a household inside and out.

632
00:30:43,410 --> 00:30:43,690
Right?

633
00:30:43,690 --> 00:30:44,760
If she marries Shen,

634
00:30:45,250 --> 00:30:47,840
your whole family gets to
live the easy life.

635
00:30:47,970 --> 00:30:48,590
But that fairy

636
00:30:48,730 --> 00:30:49,930
is a whole different story.

637
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:52,690
Aside from her academic work,
what else can she do?

638
00:30:53,080 --> 00:30:54,450
She only chews on that giant bun.

639
00:30:55,250 --> 00:30:56,790
How do you know
she chews on a giant bun?

640
00:30:57,170 --> 00:30:57,730
I can see it.

641
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:02,320
I can see exactly

642
00:31:02,320 --> 00:31:03,360
what kind of person she is.

643
00:31:04,930 --> 00:31:06,360
Think about it.

644
00:31:06,890 --> 00:31:07,860
If she cooks her meals,

645
00:31:08,210 --> 00:31:10,120
there is no time
to write letters and paint.

646
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:11,380
She can't do her academic work.

647
00:31:11,840 --> 00:31:12,280
Am I right?

648
00:31:12,490 --> 00:31:14,040
But honestly,

649
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:15,010
doing housework

650
00:31:15,890 --> 00:31:16,760
is exhausting.

651
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:18,080
We barely have time for anything,

652
00:31:18,450 --> 00:31:19,650
let alone writing letters.

653
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:21,520
It's not realistic for us.

654
00:31:22,490 --> 00:31:23,360
Yeah, that's true.

655
00:32:27,410 --> 00:32:32,800
"Let's meet again
at the painted bridge."

656
00:32:35,250 --> 00:32:42,680
"Blossoms full of spirit,
willows soft and slow."

657
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:57,930
Which one do you think I should wear?

658
00:32:58,850 --> 00:33:00,410
Grandpa, why are you picking so many?

659
00:33:00,410 --> 00:33:02,040
It's not even that formal of an event.

660
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:05,770
You know Ms. Nie's coming, right?

661
00:33:05,770 --> 00:33:07,850
Shouldn't I at least
look a little presentable?

662
00:33:13,560 --> 00:33:14,620
So, which one looks best?

663
00:33:15,010 --> 00:33:15,430
This one.

664
00:33:16,490 --> 00:33:18,090
It makes you look younger and energetic.

665
00:33:18,610 --> 00:33:19,639
Maybe this one's better.

666
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:20,290
More formal.

667
00:33:20,330 --> 00:33:20,680
And...

668
00:33:20,680 --> 00:33:22,120
Your mom says this is the one

669
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:23,450
she got on sale at the mall.

670
00:33:23,450 --> 00:33:24,120
It wasn't cheap.

671
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:24,970
Nope.

672
00:33:25,330 --> 00:33:27,010
Mom only buys
those grandpa-style shirts.

673
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:28,240
These are no good.

674
00:33:30,520 --> 00:33:31,570
- I'll just wear...
- Dad!

675
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:32,600
Zhuoran!

676
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:33,890
I'm coming.

677
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:35,370
I brought you some flowers!

678
00:33:35,370 --> 00:33:36,330
What are these?

679
00:33:36,410 --> 00:33:37,160
White magnolias!

680
00:33:37,560 --> 00:33:38,810
You like growing flowers.

681
00:33:38,810 --> 00:33:39,330
Indeed.

682
00:33:39,390 --> 00:33:40,369
These are easy to grow.

683
00:33:40,370 --> 00:33:42,080
They only need some water.

684
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:42,810
Okay.

685
00:33:42,810 --> 00:33:43,720
Thank you.

686
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:44,720
Where should I put them?

687
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:45,970
On the balcony.

688
00:33:45,970 --> 00:33:47,120
Okay.

689
00:33:47,490 --> 00:33:47,970
Right away.

690
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:48,560
Over here?

691
00:33:48,560 --> 00:33:50,140
Yes. On the balcony.
Thank you so much.

692
00:33:50,290 --> 00:33:52,240
Don't be a stranger. You're welcome.

693
00:33:52,370 --> 00:33:53,600
What are you two up to?

694
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:55,490
Why did you take out all these clothes?

695
00:33:57,410 --> 00:34:00,240
We have a full run-through
scheduled for next week.

696
00:34:00,490 --> 00:34:01,550
Ms. Nie will be there too.

697
00:34:02,810 --> 00:34:04,370
The one who wrote you letters?

698
00:34:04,490 --> 00:34:05,030
That Ms. Nie?

699
00:34:05,490 --> 00:34:05,930
Yes.

700
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:08,330
She's our literary consultant now.

701
00:34:10,520 --> 00:34:12,850
Then, go with the gray one.
It looks classy.

702
00:34:13,200 --> 00:34:13,640
Very sharp.

703
00:34:16,490 --> 00:34:16,850
Alright.

704
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:17,520
Mom.

705
00:34:18,010 --> 00:34:18,660
Leave it there.

706
00:34:20,330 --> 00:34:21,120
Put it right there.

707
00:34:21,640 --> 00:34:22,720
Wear this one, Grandpa.

708
00:34:23,240 --> 00:34:24,290
It makes you look younger.

709
00:34:24,890 --> 00:34:26,290
Didn't you say she never showed up?

710
00:34:26,490 --> 00:34:27,450
Well, now she is.

711
00:34:28,080 --> 00:34:29,120
Things have changed.

712
00:34:30,520 --> 00:34:31,200
Yeah.

713
00:34:31,810 --> 00:34:32,560
Zhuoran.

714
00:34:33,490 --> 00:34:34,720
Is it a full-dress rehearsal?

715
00:34:35,810 --> 00:34:37,970
Zhuoran, this is
turning into a big deal.

716
00:34:38,200 --> 00:34:38,770
Exactly.

717
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:40,720
It's getting pretty fancy.

718
00:34:41,290 --> 00:34:42,240
Lina, tell me something.

719
00:34:42,640 --> 00:34:44,330
When are the costumes arriving?

720
00:34:45,200 --> 00:34:46,660
Tomorrow. They will be here tomorrow.

721
00:34:47,970 --> 00:34:48,560
That's great!

722
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:50,450
But, we still have one problem.

723
00:34:51,240 --> 00:34:51,850
Lunch.

724
00:34:52,450 --> 00:34:54,200
The cafeteria is too far away.

725
00:34:54,560 --> 00:34:56,239
It's hot outside.
The seniors won't make it.

726
00:34:56,240 --> 00:34:58,020
But, we're not sure
if the cafeteria delivers.

727
00:34:58,120 --> 00:34:59,160
You can order deliveries.

728
00:34:59,590 --> 00:35:00,599
- Yeah.
- Food delivery.

729
00:35:00,600 --> 00:35:01,680
Dad, let me check the price.

730
00:35:01,810 --> 00:35:03,040
What's the budget per person?

731
00:35:03,160 --> 00:35:03,680
Thirty yuan.

732
00:35:04,520 --> 00:35:05,290
Thirty yuan.

733
00:35:05,450 --> 00:35:07,239
Thirty? That's just right
for a burger combo.

734
00:35:07,240 --> 00:35:07,810
Perfect.

735
00:35:08,680 --> 00:35:09,450
That works for me.

736
00:35:10,120 --> 00:35:12,120
They're all seniors.
Who wants to eat burgers?

737
00:35:12,120 --> 00:35:13,600
Yeah, plus takeout

738
00:35:13,850 --> 00:35:15,040
is not healthy.

739
00:35:15,040 --> 00:35:17,290
Too much oil and salt.

740
00:35:17,410 --> 00:35:19,010
Even the news says so.

741
00:35:19,330 --> 00:35:20,740
It's especially bad for the elderly.

742
00:35:21,010 --> 00:35:21,720
That's true.

743
00:35:22,410 --> 00:35:23,970
Maybe everyone
can bring their own lunch?

744
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:25,120
Not ideal.

745
00:35:25,770 --> 00:35:27,929
They rehearse so hard.
We can't even provide one meal?

746
00:35:27,930 --> 00:35:29,120
It's bad for morale.

747
00:35:32,450 --> 00:35:33,300
Let's cook ourselves.

748
00:35:33,930 --> 00:35:36,700
Mom, they actually have a budget.
We can get reimbursed.

749
00:35:36,700 --> 00:35:37,779
- Exactly.
- Reimbursement?

750
00:35:37,780 --> 00:35:40,010
You said you needed more receipts.
Just collect a few.

751
00:35:40,490 --> 00:35:41,080
I'll do it.

752
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:44,930
We're retired,
time to put our skills to use.

753
00:35:45,120 --> 00:35:45,870
They put on a show,

754
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:46,640
and

755
00:35:46,850 --> 00:35:47,490
we provide them

756
00:35:48,520 --> 00:35:49,010
with energy!

757
00:35:50,810 --> 00:35:51,680
Well said.

758
00:35:51,770 --> 00:35:52,560
It's settled, then.

759
00:35:52,810 --> 00:35:53,490
Great!

760
00:35:53,810 --> 00:35:54,199
Wonderful.

761
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:54,520
Okay.

762
00:35:54,640 --> 00:35:55,720
We'll start preparing.

763
00:35:56,890 --> 00:35:57,490
Get cooking!

764
00:35:57,490 --> 00:35:59,040
I'll follow up on the costumes.

765
00:36:02,370 --> 00:36:02,970
Grandpa.

766
00:36:04,490 --> 00:36:05,290
My mom's starting

767
00:36:06,010 --> 00:36:07,680
to act more and more like my grandma.

768
00:36:12,810 --> 00:36:13,390
Alright then,

769
00:36:14,240 --> 00:36:15,560
I'll wear the one your mom picked.

770
00:36:15,560 --> 00:36:16,639
But it doesn't look good.

771
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:17,490
What can you do?

772
00:36:21,520 --> 00:36:21,770
Okay.

773
00:36:22,010 --> 00:36:22,720
This is nice.

774
00:36:23,330 --> 00:36:23,970
It looks decent.

775
00:36:31,010 --> 00:36:32,020
- Coming!
- Open the door.

776
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:32,970
Coming!

777
00:36:36,890 --> 00:36:37,520
What's up?

778
00:36:38,240 --> 00:36:38,810
This Sunday,

779
00:36:39,370 --> 00:36:41,720
Shen's choir is having
a dress rehearsal.

780
00:36:42,930 --> 00:36:44,290
Ms. Nie's coming too.

781
00:36:44,600 --> 00:36:45,200
For real?

782
00:36:48,770 --> 00:36:50,010
I'm bringing them lunch.

783
00:36:51,330 --> 00:36:52,640
Peng Yulan,

784
00:36:52,850 --> 00:36:55,520
you might want to back out now.

785
00:37:00,410 --> 00:37:01,290
You know what?

786
00:37:01,560 --> 00:37:02,890
You need to think this through.

787
00:37:02,970 --> 00:37:05,040
Shen can't lift a thing,

788
00:37:05,040 --> 00:37:06,010
can't carry anything,

789
00:37:06,010 --> 00:37:07,450
and always mops around.

790
00:37:08,040 --> 00:37:08,410
Right?

791
00:37:08,410 --> 00:37:09,850
If something really happens,

792
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:11,850
even my Liu Debao would be more useful.

793
00:37:13,850 --> 00:37:16,160
Professor Shen is a cultured man.

794
00:37:16,640 --> 00:37:17,040
See this?

795
00:37:17,520 --> 00:37:19,200
His handwriting is beautiful.

796
00:37:19,720 --> 00:37:20,850
He's refined,

797
00:37:21,410 --> 00:37:22,640
full of knowledge,

798
00:37:23,010 --> 00:37:25,010
and always so gentle and polite.

799
00:37:26,040 --> 00:37:26,970
My ex

800
00:37:27,770 --> 00:37:28,970
was a total brute.

801
00:37:29,930 --> 00:37:32,010
He could haul 200 catties of rice
like it was nothing.

802
00:37:32,640 --> 00:37:34,520
But, the moment he picked up a book,

803
00:37:35,370 --> 00:37:36,290
he'd fall asleep.

804
00:37:37,490 --> 00:37:38,850
Back then, at the factory,

805
00:37:39,450 --> 00:37:41,490
I had the chance
to go to Beijing for training.

806
00:37:41,890 --> 00:37:43,290
I could've become an accountant.

807
00:37:43,450 --> 00:37:44,450
Yeah, I remember that.

808
00:37:46,010 --> 00:37:47,240
But he said to me,

809
00:37:48,120 --> 00:37:48,640
"Accounting?

810
00:37:49,080 --> 00:37:50,220
What's so great about that?"

811
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:53,070
Once you're an accountant,
you're stuck in the office for life."

812
00:37:54,290 --> 00:37:54,970
"You can't even

813
00:37:54,970 --> 00:37:57,330
sneak out early if you wanted to."

814
00:37:58,240 --> 00:37:59,160
And I told him,

815
00:37:59,450 --> 00:38:01,640
"The more skills you have,
the more options you have."

816
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:02,370
Exactly.

817
00:38:03,810 --> 00:38:04,770
Guess what he did?

818
00:38:06,010 --> 00:38:07,450
He slapped me across the face.

819
00:38:11,080 --> 00:38:12,490
He said I was getting wild ideas.

820
00:38:17,370 --> 00:38:18,810
I had his handprint on my face.

821
00:38:20,770 --> 00:38:22,240
It took half a month to fade.

822
00:38:32,600 --> 00:38:33,600
With him,

823
00:38:33,720 --> 00:38:36,490
there was no real
communication or understanding.

824
00:38:36,810 --> 00:38:38,490
What's the point of reasoning with him?

825
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:39,850
It's pointless.

826
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:42,080
That's just awful.

827
00:38:42,120 --> 00:38:43,290
He was so awful.

828
00:38:43,490 --> 00:38:44,850
He actually hit you?

829
00:38:47,570 --> 00:38:48,199
You know what?

830
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:49,390
You were right to divorce him.

831
00:38:49,810 --> 00:38:50,490
A right decision.

832
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:52,640
What man would hold his wife back

833
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:54,680
from improving herself?

834
00:38:55,490 --> 00:38:56,330
Unbelievable.

835
00:38:57,010 --> 00:38:57,450
You know,

836
00:38:58,410 --> 00:39:00,200
if it were Professor Shen,

837
00:39:00,720 --> 00:39:03,040
he would never have
done something like that.

838
00:39:03,290 --> 00:39:04,040
Of course not.

839
00:39:04,410 --> 00:39:06,890
Professor Shen isn't that violent.

840
00:39:07,040 --> 00:39:07,330
Indeed.

841
00:39:13,370 --> 00:39:14,080
Baoqin.

842
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:16,370
When are you guys

843
00:39:16,810 --> 00:39:18,120
going next week?

844
00:39:19,770 --> 00:39:20,560
Next Sunday,

845
00:39:21,200 --> 00:39:22,040
around noon.

846
00:39:26,810 --> 00:39:27,470
How about this?

847
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:30,490
Maybe I should just go with you.

848
00:39:31,520 --> 00:39:32,600
Peng Yulan,

849
00:39:33,040 --> 00:39:34,120
I'm totally supporting you.

850
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:35,040
I mean it.

851
00:39:35,640 --> 00:39:37,290
You should make a great impression.

852
